The Police Command in Kaduna State on Thursday, confirmed the abduction of the Vice-Chairman, All Progressives Congress (APC), Kaduna State chapter, Shu’aibu Idris-Lauge and his daughter. DAILY POST had reported that unknown gunmen abducted Idris alongside his daughter from their residence at Kwanar Zango along Zaria-Kaduna expressway. Confirming the kidnap, the Command’s Public Relations Officer, Mohammed Jalige, told journalist in Kaduna that Shu’aibu and his daughter were abducted from their Kwanar Zango residence along Kaduna-Zaria express way on Thursday morning. He said “Efforts are being made to rescue the kidnapped victims, apprehend and bring the culprits to book.” He further appealed to the public to support the Police by providing useful information that would lead to the rescue of the victims, NAN reports.